9 An Act relating to local law enforcement; creating
the Public Safety Technology Revolving Fund;
10 establishing revolving fund characteristics; deeming
funds appropriated; providing purpose for
11 expenditures; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 20m of Title 74, unless there is
17 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
19 for the Office of the Attorney General to be designated the "Public
20 Safety Technology Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a continuing
21 fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of
22 all monies received by the Office of the Attorney General as
23 designated by law. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund
24 are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1250 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Offi ce for the purpose of funding grants to local law enforcement
2 divisions to cover some of the costs associated with using
3 technology to better interface with the public. Expenditures from
4 said fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
5 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
6 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
7 payment.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
9 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC SAFETY
April 7, 2026 - DO PASS
